-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Magyar Telekom Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-06-19T15:15:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-magyar-telekom-shares-move-in-budapest.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 1.5
percent to 17,805.75 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, rose 3.8
percent to 3,777 forint. Hungary progressed toward bailout talks
with the  International Monetary Fund . Greece moved toward
forming a government and a Spanish debt sale met targets, easing
concern the European debt crisis will escalate.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTELEKOM HB), the Hungarian unit of
Deutsche Telekom AG, fell 1.1 percent to 454 forint. Erste Group
Bank cut its price target for Magyar Telekom to 470 forint from
500 forint and reduced its 2012 dividend estimate for the
company to 40 forint from 50 forint. Erste raised Magyar
Telekom’s recommendation to hold from reduce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
